  "text": "The exact mechanism of genome amplification has not been elucidated, but there has long been evidence that it might differ from the bidirectional theta mode characteristic of maintenance replication [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . A breakthrough in the study of HPV replication was the observation that differentiation-dependent genome amplification required the cellular ATM DNA damage response and repair (DDR) pathway [CITATION_3] . This finding opened up the possibility that genomes might be amplified in differentiated cells by a recombination-dependent replication mode supported by the DDR response.",
